   Transportation Administrative Services Center (TASC)
   DOT vacancy announcements are also available through the TASC DOT
   Connection Fax-On-Demand system at (202) 366-9397 or outside the
   Washington D.C. area call (800) 525-2878.

   Federal Government jobs
   USAJOBS is the United States Government's official source of job and
   employment information in most federal agencies. The site also has a
   resume builder as well as online employment application for some jobs.

   Also visit Access Americas The Job Page for more information on federal
   jobs, student jobs, Americas job bank, innovative job pages, and more.

   Students can also find valuable information about applying for jobs in
   the government at www.studentjobs.gov

   Transportation Education and Careers
   The Transportation Education and Careers site is designed for the
   future transportation workforce. Students have access to career
   information and resources for occupations in the transportation
   industry.

   Occupational Outlook Handbook (U.S. Department of Labor site)
   This site includes Career Guide to Industries and descriptions of
   various occupations. Descriptions include categories like nature of
   work, working conditions, training, job outlook, earnings and more.
   This link takes you directly to Transportation and Material Moving
   occupations section..
